reviews.review_text:
A lovely recording Wonderful MIDI explorations and lots of new songs. Another great 89 show...

Thanks for sharing it with us!

Adam Katz RIP
sorry the sound quality is low

IKO IKO Sound quality on this is decent....well worth the listen for the Good Times Roll > IKO IKO which are both filled with tons of energy, especially IKO.  Crowd very into it.  Been listening to it in my car all week.  This first set is better than second set...kind of weird to say that for an '89 show.  Row Jimmy is great and a first set ending Standing On The Moon is quite inspring here....Jerry nails the lyrics throughout.....this was the last time they closed out the first set with Standing On The Moon...simply amazing version, but not best ever.  Little Light is great as were any songs Brent sang.  Miss you Brent and Jerry forever!
